review: The Grand stands out for its exceptional service and stunning location. Our room offered panoramic views of the sea, and the food was divine. The attention to detail in every aspect of our stay was remarkable.

Our weekend at The Grand was nothing short of spectacular. The rooms are spacious and elegantly furnished, and the staff made us feel incredibly welcome. The highlight was the gourmet breakfast that set us up for the day.
A truly 5-star experience at The Grand in Brighton! From the opulent decor to the serene spa facilities, everything was perfect. The staff were always on hand to assist, making us feel like royalty.

What an unforgettable stay at The Grand! The luxury and comfort of our room, combined with the friendliness of the staff, made our visit to Brighton perfect. The dining experience was top-notch, with exquisite flavors.

The Grand in Brighton exceeded all our expectations! The sea view from our room was breathtaking, and the staff went above and beyond to make our stay special. The cleanliness and attention to detail were impeccable.

Unfortunately, The Grand in Brighton did not live up to the hype. Our room was cramped and the decor felt outdated. We encountered several issues with the service, which dampened our overall experience.

We were disappointed with our stay at The Grand. Despite its promising location, the room was uncomfortable and lacked basic amenities. The service was slow, and the staff seemed indifferent to our needs.
Expected more from The Grand. The room was not as advertised, with minimal facilities and a lack of cleanliness. The overall atmosphere was not welcoming, and the value for money just wasn't there.
Our experience at The Grand was less than ideal. The room felt neglected, with visible wear and tear. The staff interaction was minimal, making it hard to resolve issues we faced during our stay.

Disheartened by our visit to The Grand. The room was small and poorly lit, with an unappealing view. The service lacked the personal touch we expected, leaving much to be desired in terms of hospitality.

The Grand in Brighton offers a mix of positives and negatives. The location is excellent, with easy access to the beach. However, the rooms could benefit from some modernization. The staff were friendly, though occasionally seemed busy.

A decent stay at The Grand, with some room for improvement. The building itself is impressive, and the views are lovely. The room was clean but basic, and the service varied throughout our stay. Worth considering for its location.

The Grand has its charms, particularly its historic facade and prime location. The room was adequate, though not particularly luxurious. Service was good on the whole, though it lacked consistency at times.

Mixed feelings about The Grand. It's well-situated in Brighton, offering good access to local attractions. The room was comfortable but felt a bit dated. The staff were mostly helpful, but service could be slow.

Our stay at The Grand was good overall, with a few caveats. The seafront location is fantastic, but the room, while clean, was somewhat uninspiring. The staff were pleasant, though not always prompt in their service.

Disheartened by our visit to The Grand. The room was small and poorly lit, with an unappealing view. The service lacked the personal touch we expected, leaving much to be desired in terms of hospitality.
Dining at The Grand was a culinary delight, with a variety of international dishes prepared to perfection. The ambiance of the restaurant added to the experience, making every meal memorable.
The spa at The Grand is a haven of relaxation. The range of treatments available and the professionalism of the staff were outstanding. It's a perfect retreat for anyone looking to unwind.
The service at The Grand sets a new standard for luxury hotels. Every request was met with promptness and a smile, making us feel valued and taken care of throughout our stay.
The noise levels at The Grand were unbearable at times, with thin walls allowing sound to travel easily from neighboring rooms and the hallway.
While the location of The Grand is convenient, parking was a nightmare. The hotel offers limited spots, and we ended up parking a considerable distance away.
The Wi-Fi at The Grand was incredibly slow and unreliable, which was frustrating for both leisure and business-related needs.
The Grand has a fantastic gym with state-of-the-art equipment. However, it would benefit from extended opening hours to accommodate early risers and late-night fitness enthusiasts.
The rooftop bar at The Grand offers stunning views and a great selection of drinks. Prices are on the higher side, but the ambiance somewhat justifies the cost.
Check-in and check-out processes at The Grand were efficient, but the hotel lacks the personal touch that makes a stay memorable. It felt more transactional than welcoming.
